ange and continuity in one town, Dismantling Apartheid is a compelling preview of future social relations in South Africa.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aApartheidzSouth AfricazMthatha. 4aAfrican Hist & Diaspora. 4aAnthropology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172183040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501721830423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501721830/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles